  "prompt": "How can I know in which field I'm interested?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to explore and discover your interests:\n\n1. Self-reflection methods\n- Make a list of activities you enjoy\n- Think about subjects that excite you\n- Recall what you loved doing as a child\n- Consider your natural strengths and skills\n\n2. Practical exploration strategies\n- Take online personality and career assessments\n- Read diverse books and articles\n- Watch documentaries and educational videos\n- Listen to podcasts in different fields\n- Attend workshops and seminars\n\n3. Hands-on approaches\n- Try different hobbies\n- Volunteer in various organizations\n- Take online courses\n- Shadow professionals in different careers\n- Attend career fairs\n- Do informational interviews\n\n4. Academic/Professional approaches\n- Take diverse elective courses\n- Explore interdisciplinary programs\n- Do internships in different fields\n- Network with professionals\n- Join student organizations\n\n5. Internal indicators\n- Notice what makes you lose track of time\n- Identify topics that spark curiosity\n- Pay attention to activities that energize you\n- Recognize subjects you naturally discuss passionately\n\n6. Digital resources\n- Use career exploration websites\n- Take free online skill assessments\n- Follow diverse professionals on social media\n- Join online communities related to various fields\n\nRemember, discovering your interests is a journey of continuous exploration and self-discovery.",
